text:
Me as a Legion Main , suffered a lot.
(Legion was to hard to loop that nobody wanted to go against them , quickly injures people and can locate them with much ease and one of his starting perks "Discordance" shows you where two or more survivors are and so their power comes into good action)
But in the matter of perks , I would have recommended The Clown. ts rather simple to get used to his bottles and are annoyingly effective if thrown correctly , also has two of the best perks (In my opinion) "Bamboozle" and "Pop goes the weasle" 
But for ranking up your characters fast The cannibal's perk "BBQ and Chilly" is the best one , it gives extra bloodpoints for hooking survivors and shows you the aura of survivors further away from you , his power too is very effective and simple.
(Im in Red Ranks for both so I can speak with convince out of the hours I wasted in the game)

text:
Gura, you mentioned you were seeing blurring with the monitors in Muse Dash. From what you've said about your previous monitor getting darker when you sat low, it was a TN panel which has very fast pixel changes and your new curved MSI monitors are VA panels which can struggle with dark to light color changes. 
The best you can do to reduce the blurring is make sure it's running at max refresh rate (144Hz+) and turn up the "Response Time" setting to "Fast" or "Fastest" and make sure Muse Dash runs at max FPS so Gsync doesn't drag the refresh rate down.
If you're still inclined to have curved monitors, the Samsung G7 comes in 32" versions and largely don't have this problem.
